# TypeScript

## Strictness

- `strict: true` everywhere; no `any` without a comment explaining why
- Prefer `unknown` over `any` at boundaries
- Use `satisfies` for config objects; export public types from `packages/core`

## Style

- Named exports over default exports
- Async functions must handle errors; never empty `catch`
- Use `Result<T, E>` or thrown domain errors — pick one per layer, stay consistent

## File layout

```typescript
// 1. types
// 2. constants
// 3. helpers
// 4. main export
```

## Naming

- `ScanRule`, `ToolAdapter`, `MemoryRecord` — match TECHNICAL.md domain terms
- Files: `kebab-case.ts`; types/interfaces: `PascalCase`

## Tests

- Colocate: `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts`
- Fixtures in `fixtures/`; never use real user paths in tests
